<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum nitidibaccatum" order="Solanales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitidibaccatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Solanum nitidibaccatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a disturbance loving species, usually found growing along roadsides in the shade of trees and shrubs, and in rocky and sandy soil between (0-)1,200 and 2,500 m elevation. It is a common weed of agriculture and is often found growing in sandy soil in seasonal washes (arroyos).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
